DAY 1 — COMPUTER ARCHITECTURE
--------------------------------
Introduction :
--------------
Computer architecture defines how hardware components work together to execute programs.
  
Basic Components :
-------------------
1. CPU (Central Processing Unit):
Brain of the computer
Executes instructions
Performs calculations
  
2. RAM (Random Access Memory):
Temporary memory
Stores currently running programs
Volatile (data lost when power off)
  
3. Cache Memory:
Very fast memory inside CPU
Stores frequently used data
Types: L1, L2, L3
  
4. Disk (HDD/SSD)
Permanent storage
Stores OS, files, applications
  
Data Flow:
-----------
Disk → RAM → Cache → CPU

Memory Hierarchy:
-----------------
Cache (fastest, smallest)
RAM (medium)
Disk (slowest, largest)
  
Why Cache?
-----------
Reduces CPU waiting time
Improves performance
  
CPU Internals:
--------------
ALU (Arithmetic Logic Unit)
Control Unit
Registers
Virtual Memory
Uses disk as extra RAM
Context Switching
CPU switches between tasks
